body:
For reference, the following gives an `AddressSanitizer: stack-use-after-scope`, because the argument was passed with `std::ref`, but does not if the argument is not passed with `std::ref`.

<details><summary>`std::thread`/`std::ref` test</summary>

```cpp
#include <chrono>
#include <iostream>
#include <thread>

void fun(const std::string &a) {
  std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds{10});
  std::cout << a << std::endl;
}

int main() {
  std::thread a;
  {
    std::string s{"s"};
    a = std::thread{fun, std::ref(s)};
  }
  a.join();
}
```

</details>

